{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.10",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 10",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 10 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:1",
      "text": "My soul is weary of my life, I will let go my speech against myself, I will speak in the bitterness of my soul.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:2",
      "text": "I will say to God: Do not condemn me: tell me why thou judgest me so?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:3",
      "text": "Doth it seem good to thee that thou shouldst calumniate me, and oppress me, the work of thy own hands, and help the counsel of the wicked?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:4",
      "text": "Hast thou eyes of flesh: or, shalt thou see as man seeth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:5",
      "text": "Are thy days as the days of man, and are thy years as the times of men:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:6",
      "text": "That thou shouldst inquire after my iniquity, and search after my sin?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:7",
      "text": "And shouldst know that I have done no wicked thing, whereas there is no man that can deliver out of thy hand?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:8",
      "text": "Thy hands have made me, and fashioned me wholly round about, and dost thou thus cast me down headlong on a sudden?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:9",
      "text": "Remember, I beseech thee, that thou hast made me as the clay, and thou wilt bring me into dust",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:10",
      "text": "Hast thou not milked me as milk, and curdled me like cheese?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:11",
      "text": "Thou hast clothed me with skin and flesh: thou hast put me together with bones and sinews:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:12",
      "text": "Thou hast granted me life and mercy, and thy visitation hath preserved my spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:13",
      "text": "Although thou conceal these things in thy heart, yet I know that thou rememberest all things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:14",
      "text": "If I have sinned, and thou hast spared me for an hour: why dost thou not suffer me to be clean from my iniquity?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:15",
      "text": "And if I be wicked, woe unto me: and if just, I shall not lift up my head, being filled with affliction and misery.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:16",
      "text": "And for pride thou wilt take me as a lioness, and returning, thou tormentest me wonderfully.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:17",
      "text": "Thou renewest thy witnesses against me, and multipliest thy wrath upon me, and pains war against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:18",
      "text": "Why didst thou bring me forth out of the womb? O that I had been consumed, that eye might not see me!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:19",
      "text": "I should have been as if I had not been, carried from the womb to the grave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:20",
      "text": "Shall not the fewness of my days be ended shortly? Suffer me, therefore, that I may lament my sorrow a little:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:21",
      "text": "Before I go and return no more, to a land that is dark and covered with the mist of death:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.10.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:22",
      "text": "A land of misery and darkness, where the shadow of death, and no order, but everlasting horror dwelleth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
